<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 32. Natural habitats of New Caledonian agapophytine stiletto flies A Mount Aoupinie, rainforest, habitat of C. monteithi sp. nov. B Mount Ningua, rainforest, habitat of J. nubilosus sp. nov. C Mount Mandjelia, habitat of C. grandiosus sp. nov. (photographs by Michael E. Irwin)." , "Figure 31. Natural habitats of New Caledonian agapophytine stiletto flies A Riviere Bleue Reserve, sclerophyll forest and maquis scrub, habitat of C. chazeaui sp. nov., C. grandiosus sp. nov., C. schlingeri sp. nov., and J. nubilosus sp. nov. B Pindai Peninsula, tropical dry forest, habitat of C. webbi sp. nov. C Mount Dzumac, rainforest, habitat of J. nubilosus sp. nov. D Mount Dore, rainforest and dry sclerophyll forest E Mount Dore, Malaise trap in flyway (photographs by Michael E. Irwin)." , "Figure 22. Distribution of Calophytus spp. collecting records throughout New Caledonia. Provinces are labelled and ecoregions delineated by colour." , "Figure 4. Phylogenetic placement of Calophytus gen. nov. and Jeanchazeauia gen. nov. in Agapophytinae based on supermatrix analysis of DNA sequence data. Figure modified after Winterton et al. (2016: fig. 3)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471342" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471341" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471332" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471320" .

